description:
drh added on 2022-12-06 19:58:43:
Consider the following SQL:

.echo on
.mode qbox
CREATE VIEW dual(dummy) AS SELECT 'X';
CREATE TABLE t0(a INT, b TEXT);
INSERT INTO t0 VALUES(1,'one');
CREATE VIEW t1      AS SELECT a, b FROM t0 UNION ALL SELECT 2, 2;
CREATE VIEW t2(a,b) AS SELECT a, b FROM t0 UNION ALL SELECT 2, 2;
PRAGMA table_info(t1);
PRAGMA table_info(t2);
SELECT *, typeof(b) FROM t1;
SELECT *, typeof(b) FROM t2;
SELECT *, typeof(b) FROM dual, t1;
SELECT *, typeof(b) FROM dual, t2;

The two views t1 and t2 have different column affinities, as can
be seen in the output of the PRAGMA table_info statements.  The
t1 view has affinities taken from the SELECT statement that defines
the view.  The t2 view has numeric affinity on all columns.  This
can make a difference in results as is shown by the
final two queries - the joins against dual.
This issue appears to go back to version 3.9.0 when the ability to
assign names to the columns of views was first added.
